<item>
            <title>[RAT-275] Update httpclient to fix CVE-2020-13956 once a new doxia-core release is available</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/RAT-275</link>
                <project id="12310750" key="RAT">Apache RAT</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Once a newer doxia version is available update to it in order to fix:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JAVA-ORGAPACHEHTTPCOMPONENTS-1016906&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://snyk.io/vuln/SNYK-JAVA-ORGAPACHEHTTPCOMPONENTS-1016906&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Remediation&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Remediation&lt;/h2&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Upgrade &lt;tt&gt;org.apache.httpcomponents:httpclient&lt;/tt&gt; to version 4.5.13, 5.0.3 or higher.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;Currently the most up2date doxia uses v4.5.8 of httpclient.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;a name=&quot;Update&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Update&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The branch &quot;update-doxia-tools&quot; tries to update some other outdated components in RAT as well ....&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;2021-06-21: Upcoming release of doxia stuff v1.10 ....&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
